Session changes (v0.9):

color_grade:
- SAT_SKY 1.20→1.30 — deeper sky blue, stronger contrast against treeline
- WHITE_B 0.90→0.93 — less aggressive blue pull on highlights/sky, reduces overall yellow cast

veil:
- VEIL_TINT_G 1.06→1.00 — removed green component from veil tint (was causing teal sky)
- VEIL_TINT_B 0.94→0.97 — eased blue suppression, less yellow bias overall
- Sky exclusion gate added: blue-dominant pixels (sky) skip veil lerp entirely
  `float sky_dom = saturate((col.b - max(col.r, col.g)) * 8.0); float not_sky = 1.0 - sky_dom;`

halation:
- sat_gate smoothstep(0.04, 0.16)→(0.08, 0.20) — sunlit white buildings were triggering halation
  Warm-white concrete post-color-grade had just enough saturation to bleed through at 0.04.
  Tightened to 0.08 — white/near-neutral surfaces excluded, genuine chromatic sources unaffected.

housekeeping:
- Removed: gzw_depth_apply.fx, gzw_depth_gather.fx (unused), gzw_foliage_light.fx.bak
- Added: gzw_grain.fx (shelved — Vision3-style luma-weighted grain, FRAME_COUNT animated)
- Added: INSTALL.md (Linux/vkBasalt + Windows/ReShade installation guide)

Session changes (v0.8):

olofssonian_zone_contrast:
- TOE_STRENGTH 0.40→0.37→0.40 — tested lower, reverted; blue stem tint compensates visually
- TOE_TINT_B 0.028→0.034 — more blue in dark shadow tint
- SHADOW_TINT_B 0.038→0.050 — more blue on dark chromatic surfaces (bark/earth at night)
- GRADE_R 0.985→0.996 — less red pull, fixes blue cast on neutral surfaces (concrete, road)
- Saturation gate floor tightened: smoothstep(0.08→0.12, 0.22) on TOE_TINT and SHADOW_TINT
- Three-way median blend: median pivot now active (was stored but unused)
  Dark pixels blend dark→mid, bright pixels blend mid→bright, quadratic outer weight preserves shadow depth
- Frame-jittered Halton: VanDerCorput replaced with pre-baked 128-point table (kHalton[])
  Array lookup replaces per-sample runtime math. Window slides by FRAME_COUNT % 128.
  Effective coverage ≈1600 unique positions over smoothing window. Output identical.

color_grade:
- LEAF_WARM 0.30→0.36 — warmer, less blue on bright foliage
- LEAF_COOL 0.38→0.32 — less blue on dark foliage
- SAT_GREEN 1.28→1.30 — slight green saturation bump
- SAT_SKY 1.30→1.20 — sky was over-saturated
- SAT_MAX 0.80→0.85 — restored from user change during previous session
- Film matrix +20% tested and reverted — added visible warm tint across all chromatic surfaces.
  Values restored to original: FILM_RG 0.044, FILM_RB 0.010, FILM_GR 0.024, FILM_GB 0.033, FILM_BR 0.010, FILM_BG 0.052

promist:
- DIFFUSE_LUMA_LO 0.45→0.50 — diffuse activates later, reduces bloom on concrete walls

sharpen:
- SHARPEN_STRENGTH restored to 0.28 (was changed to 0.20 in previous session)
- SHARPEN_LUMA_LO restored to 0.18 (was changed to 0.25 in previous session)
- CONTRAST_LO/HI unchanged at 0.05/0.15

foliage_light (efficiency):
- Silver rim: 8 neighbor samples → 4 cardinal only. Visual output unchanged.

halation (efficiency):
- Vertical blur moved to half-res (new BlurV pass + HalationBlurVTex).
  Was: vertical blur ran at full resolution (expensive).
  Now: all blur contained at half-res, Apply pass is single sample + math.
  ~75% reduction in vertical blur cost. Visual output unchanged.
